wikipedia_page.main: Lieutenant-Colonel John Davie  (3 March 1921 – 29 June 2015) was a British army officer who served on an anti-aircraft battery during the Siege of Malta and later won the Military Cross fighting communist insurgents during the Malayan Emergency.

response: John Davie (1640–1710) was an English merchant from Bideford, Devon.
